{
  "stem": "893.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Based on our birth certificate, we were able to go to the police station and secure a-- a-- an ID card, without pictures.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They gave us-- everyone-- it was such a big rush for everyone to get the ID cards, so they didn't really-- we just went in.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We showed our birth certificate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We filled out some forms, and based on that they issued a-- an ID card.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the Slovakian agent that was a Hlinka guard-- it was the equivalent of an SS person in Germany, approached me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I showed him my ID card.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He gave it back to me, found it in order.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It said that I was Roman Catholic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then the German SS person came, who must've been a Slovakian nationalist, but they were the German minority who lived in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He also gave it back to me, didn't find anything wrong with me, with my appearance, or with anything.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then my father was sitting next to me, came to my father, the Slovakian took his ID card, and he gave it back to him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When the German came to my father, he asked him in German when he was baptized.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN], meaning when he was baptized.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He made-believe he doesn't understand German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Had he understood him, he would have given himself right away-- away, because the Germans-- the Jews were the ones who spoke German, Slovakian, and Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Slovakians, if they were not German-- of German extraction, they didn't speak German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They didn't even understand German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he called his Slovakian counterpart over.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew right away that that's-- that that's not good, because my father didn't speak Slovakian.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He just spoke a little bit, just like we speak Spanish here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he asked him in Slovakian when he was baptized.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
